# Project Layout (Do Not Deviate)
spectre/
├── main.py                  # CLI entry point only
├── core/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── orchestrator.py      # Runs modules in sequence, assembles JSON
│   └── schema.py            # Pydantic output models (SpectreResult, ModuleResult)
├── modules/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── base.py              # AbstractModule base class
│   ├── financial.py         # Module 1: Financial Fortress (edgartools)
│   ├── ip.py                # Module 2: Legal Minefield (patent-client)
│   ├── sentiment.py         # Module 3: Psychological Atmosphere (VADER/TextBlob)
│   ├── porters.py           # Module 4: Porter's Five Forces (edgartools)
│   ├── vrio.py              # Module 5: VRIO Framework (edgartools)
│   └── pestel.py            # Module 6: PESTEL Model (edgartools)
├── utils/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── proxy.py             # Rotating proxy manager
│   ├── rate_limiter.py      # Respectful rate-limiting decorator
│   └── logger.py            # Structured logging (structlog)
├── config/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   └── settings.py          # Pydantic BaseSettings — all config via env vars
├── tests/
│   ├── unit/
│   └── integration/
├── pyproject.toml
└── .env.example

# Module Plugin Contract
Every module in `modules/` MUST inherit from `modules/base.py::AbstractModule`.
AbstractModule defines: `name: str`, `run(ticker: str) -> ModuleResult`, `validate() -> bool`.
The orchestrator calls modules by iterating over registered AbstractModule subclasses.
This is the plugin architecture — adding a new module = new file + register in orchestrator.